text:
Riverside Drive, east side, north from 138th to and including 137th Streets, showing the collapse of building under construction, due to a tornado, in which one person was killed and two injured.
June 26, 1905.
NEG.2855

folder: 136th Street and Riverside Drive, Manhattan, N.Y.
text:
The collapse of a building under construction at West 136th Street
and Riverside Drive; caused by a Tornado at 2 p.m.
June 26, 1905.

title: Fires, accidents and tragedies - [Collapse of a building caused by tornado.]
